content.description: Start in cracks on lower face 3 feet right of the lamp. Continue on rib to small pine tree. Page 53 route 6 in the DL guidebook 3rd edition.
content.protection: Top rope. Thin gear if any.
content.location: Aladdin’s Castle main formation left of the main tower.

content.description: Found on an isolated little buttress above and left of the main U-Haul area at the same level as Alladin's Castle but more to the east.  This climb is just right of the route "First Aid".  Climb a neat fractured rib up the level of the bottom of a nice fist crack which the climber shifts right to gain.  Climb the fist crack and move right slightly again and pull the various edges and slopers above to finish off the last 15 feet.
content.protection: Small stoppers and cams behind the fractured rib at the start either side.  2 #3 BD cams protect the fist crack.  The top 15 is blank.
content.location: Found on an isolated little buttress above and left of the main U-Haul area at the same level as Alladin's Castle but more to the east.  This climb is just right of the route "First Aid".

content.description: Three variations to this, go left for 5.6, pull the over hang for 5.10+ and go right for 5.5
content.location: Center of the wall, starts with obvious crack system.

content.description:
Start at the base of the rounded corner to the right of the major dihedral.  Devious moves get you established on the face, powerful compression allows you to move up. 

  Where this route meets Three Wishes, finish either up the nose or up the cracks to the right.
content.location: The rounded nose to the right of the major dihedral, Three Wishes.

content.description: Up the surprisingly tenuous crack - you seldom have more than one good hold at a time.  At the break, cut left, right, or go straight up (the latter is probably the least appealing option).
content.protection: Thin gear through the crux - ballnuts are useful here, but small nuts will do.
content.location: The thin crack left of the major dihedral

climbs.name: First Aid
climbs.fa: Doug Hemken, Heinke Frerichs, Burt Lindquist, Dave Erickson

content.description:
Start on the left side of the face. Traverse along the crack as the face gets steeper and the feet get smaller.  Fire up the final crack on somewhat rounded holds. 

  When you reopen the deep gash in your finger (from a kitchen accident), you may need aid to finish this route.  You definitely need your fingers for this route.
content.protection: Mostly small cams and nuts.  A couple of large cams makes it easy to set a belay anchor.
content.location: Up and slightly left from U-Haul.  To climber's right (east) from Aladdin's Castle, just out of sight.

pathTokens: East Bluff 02 - East of the Quarry

content.description: This is the tallest of the Near East crags, and actually located above the eastern corner of the quarry floor.  I have yet to see another party here.
